---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

export const prerender = true;

const updated = "June 26, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Pumkin"
  description="The terms for using Pumkin: the MIT license grant, third-party components, warranty disclaimer, and liability."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="container legal">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of Pumkin, free and open-source desktop software from
      <strong>Software For Humans, LLC</strong>, operated by Lewis LaBrie ("we", "us"). By using the
      software you agree to them. Questions:
      <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>1. License</h2>
    <p>
      Pumkin is released under the <strong>MIT License</strong>. It is free — there is nothing to
      buy and no recurring fee. You may use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense,
      and sell copies of the software, subject to the terms of the MIT License, which is included
      with the source. The full source is available on
      <a href="https://github.com/zgpbts79ws-dev/pumkin">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Third-party components</h2>
    <p>
      Pumkin runs AI models through <strong>Ollama</strong> and connects to tools via the Model
      Context Protocol (MCP). You are responsible for installing and running those components, for
      the models you choose, and for any MCP tools or servers you connect. We don't control the
      output of any model, and model output may be inaccurate — review it before relying on it.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Your responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You use Pumkin and any tools you connect to it lawfully and at your own risk.</li>
      <li>
        Agents can take real actions through the tools you give them. Pumkin includes an approval
        step for tool calls; you are responsible for what you approve and for what your agents do.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Warranty disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Pumkin is provided <strong>"as is"</strong>, without warranties of any kind, express or
      implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
      It is early-stage software (v0.x) and may contain bugs. We don't warrant that it will be
      uninterrupted or error-free. This does not exclude any warranty that cannot be excluded under
      applicable law.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect, incidental, special,
      or consequential damages, or for loss of data, profits, or business, arising from your use of
      Pumkin. Because the software is provided free of charge, our total liability to you for any
      claim relating to it is limited to zero. Nothing here limits liability that cannot be limited
      by law.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update Pumkin and these terms over time. Material changes to these terms will be
      reflected by the "last updated" date above. Continued use after a change means you accept it.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the <strong>Commonwealth of Virginia, United States</strong>,
      without regard to conflict-of-law rules, and subject to any mandatory consumer-protection rights of
      the country where you live.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Software For Humans, LLC — Virginia, United States. Email <a href="mailto:hi@pumkin.app">hi@pumkin.app</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-nav"><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy →</a></p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal { max-width: 720px; padding-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 4rem; }
  .legal h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal .updated { color: var(--brand-fg-muted); font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .legal h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin-top: 2.25rem; margin-bottom: 0.625rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { line-height: 1.7; color: var(--brand-fg); }
  .legal p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .legal ul { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; padding-left: 1.4rem; }
  .legal li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .legal a { color: var(--brand-accent-quiet); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal-nav { margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--brand-border); }
</style>
